RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRIPOLINA settled near the rear in the beginning, was nudged on for more entering the turn to get better position inside behind the frontrunner, waited on the rail to pounce through the turn, shifted outside just off the fence for the drive, was full of run in upper stretch, ran greenly drifting inwards under left handed urging in mid stretch clearing to the lead and was drawing away convincingly crossing the finish line. HOCKEY prompted inside in the early stages of the race, dropped back losing positions between rivals at the three furlong marker, regrouped to rally in the two path at the top of the lane and surged late to the place share at the finish in a photo. CALLE REINA stalked three deep in midpack outside rivals at the half, kept pace with the leaders running three wide through the turn, shifted out widest in the four path for the drive and finished up evenly in deep stretch for a minor role. MOMUNNYFOR RO tracked the top pair down the back straight, offered a brief run three wide seven sixteenths from the wire, chased the pacesetter on the turn, was in the hunt for a share turning for home and yielded between runners at the furlong marker. MAJESTIC APPEAL was off slow on the break, trailed the field down the backstretch, could not reach contention running through the turn and showed late interest on the fence to be involved for the minors at the finish.

OH PEANUTS was squeezed at the start to trail down the backside, could not make any headway throughout the turn and was not involved running on the fence to the wire.

SPANISH SERENADE was fractious in the gate, forwardly-placed three wide in pursuit of the leader, dropped back steadily on the far turn and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GO WITH GUSTO settled in midfield three deep in the beginning, was on hold inside at the seven sixteenths marker, kept pace with the leaders on the rail in the turn, rallied inside at the top of the stretch, swung outside to the six path off the tiring front leaders for clear running room in the final eighth and surged late for the victory. ARASHI tracked between foes in the second flight, advanced smartly down the back straight, put in a bold move around horses three wide at the three furlong marker, loomed in the four path turning for home and stubbornly finished between runners for second money. WHY EM SEA AY set the fractions for this race at every pole, opened up on chasing rivals in mid stretch but was caught late losing positions nearing the wire. ROYAL HUDSON was nestled on the rail throughout the race keeping a close eye on the leaders, slipped up the fence to pose a threat at the top of the lane inside but needed another gear late to threaten the top pair at the wire. VUCCHELLA stalked near the rear on the first turn, advanced smartly outside horses down the backstretch, was rouse midpoint on the far turn gaining on rivals, was in the mix for a share in the three path turning for home, was steadied sharply at the furlong marker and could not regroup late. THEFRONTIERSMAN prompted four wide on the first turn, pressure the frontrunner down the backstretch, could not quicken with others at the quarter pole and faded between foes in the final sixteenth. AWESOME ENTRY travelled in midpack on the rail in the first turn, settled near the back on the fence into the turn, switched to the outside offering a brief run until the top of the stretch and could not be a factor running to the wire. THAT GIRL ARTEMUS was in the second flight outside three deep in the early going, was shuffled back on the far turn and could not make a presence through the stretch run. CATHOLIC JACKIE stalked near the back on the rail, was urged for more to catch up with runners entering the far turn and had little to give in the stretch drive. JOKESTAR hesitated at the break trailing the field in the beginning, was roused down the backstretch, showed little interest and had nothing the show for running down the lane. RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRICELESS WILL settled off the leaders and ahead of the back half of the field tracking from the two path, advanced on the turn niggled along, shifted four wide coming the quarter pole, struck the lead at the top of the stretch, moved clear, drifted out late and just held a rival. STAR SIGN settled off the pace, went about three to four wide on the turn, fanned six wide coming out of that bend, had aim on the leader, gained steadily through the lane despite being carried out late. HAVE A SOUPER DAY raced near mid-pack inside, went in the two to three path on the turn, came out in the lane and ran on. BIG EXECUTIVE settled at the back off the inside, altered out for room near the furlong grounds and finished up well but needed more and missed show. U S ARMY CORPS was at the rear inside, saved ground on the turn, faced traffic in upper stretch, altered four wide nearing the eighth pole and had the best late stride but with far too much to do. HICKSY raced mid-pack off the pace going four to five wide on the turn, moved out a bit turning for home, ran on. LIGHT THE LAMP got away well but settled off the pace to stalk, swept three wide on the turn taking a narrow lead past the five-sixteenths outside runners, weakened in the stretch. BEAU GUEST raced outside at the back going four wide on the turn and put to urging late on that bend, came out a bit for the drive, failed to rally. MAAKWA was urged from the break, moved forward inside quickly to the lead and clear, set the pace, faltered and faded. CITRUS BOY was coaxed forward from the break, chased the leader, drew to within range between runners coming to the five-sixteenths, faded in the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME BOURBON made an early move to get a great inside position at the five eighths marker, sat behind the leaders waiting to pounce on the turn, bullied way through between runners at the top of the stretch and gamely finished up drawing clear at the wire. COLONEL MUSTARD settled near the back three wide, was nudged throughout the turn keeping pace with horses, shifted five wide having a clear path for run turning for home, loomed the threat in upper stretch but was outfinished by the winner late and settled for second best in a solid effort. BLAST IN THE SNOW took command from the start, had a slim advantage setting the pace on the turn, was clinging to the lead in upper stretch, collared at the furlong marker and gave way to the top two still holding easily for third at the finish. UNCAPTURED MOMENT was nestled behind the leaders on the rail in the beginning, could not keep position with five eighths to go inside, shuffled back to near the back into the turn, recover to be in the hunt four wide at the top of the lane and ran evenly in the final furlong for a minor share. BASKETBALL JONES prompted between down the back straight, chased between foes on the turn, could not find more turning for home with rivals on either side and faded at the eighth pole. RENEGADE SERENADE broke slow to trail considerably down the backstretch, could not catch up to the field on the turn and showed late interest to pass tired runners down the lane. DISSECTOLOGIST stalked four deep down the backside, offered a mild turn of foot four wide around runners three furlongs to the wire, swung out widest in the seven path to be have a chance for share of the prize, could not sustain the run and tired at the furlong pole. MUSICAL SPELL pressed the issue three wide in the early stages, could not maintain position with other rivals were quickening with five sixteenths to go, angled six wide for the stretch run and retreated in upper stretch.
